## Objective
Implement the three-tier design token system with CSS custom properties, dark mode support, and base styles.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Primitive tokens (colors, spacing, typography, borders, shadows)
- [ ] Semantic tokens (surface, text, interactive, status colors)
- [ ] Component tokens (button, card, input specific)
- [ ] Dark mode via `.dark` class on `<html>`
- [ ] Dark mode toggle persisted to localStorage
- [ ] System preference detection (`prefers-color-scheme`)
- [ ] CSS reset/normalize applied
- [ ] Focus states with `--color-focus` token
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected
- [ ] Organization brand token overrides work

## Token Structure

### Tier 1: Primitives (`primitives.css`)
```css
:root {
  /* Colors */
  --color-gray-50: #f9fafb;
  --color-gray-900: #111827;
  --color-blue-500: #3b82f6;
  /* ... */

  /* Spacing */
  --space-1: 0.25rem;
  --space-2: 0.5rem;
  --space-4: 1rem;
  /* ... */

  /* Typography */
  --font-sans: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
  --text-sm: 0.875rem;
  --text-base: 1rem;
  /* ... */
}
```

### Tier 2: Semantic (`semantic.css`)
```css
:root {
  --color-surface: var(--color-white);
  --color-surface-secondary: var(--color-gray-50);
  --color-text-primary: var(--color-gray-900);
  --color-text-secondary: var(--color-gray-600);
  --color-interactive: var(--color-blue-500);
  --color-interactive-hover: var(--color-blue-600);
  --color-border: var(--color-gray-200);
  --color-focus: var(--color-blue-500);
}

.dark {
  --color-surface: var(--color-gray-900);
  --color-surface-secondary: var(--color-gray-800);
  --color-text-primary: var(--color-gray-50);
  --color-text-secondary: var(--color-gray-400);
  --color-border: var(--color-gray-700);
}
```

### Tier 3: Component (`components.css`)
```css
:root {
  --button-bg: var(--color-interactive);
  --button-text: var(--color-white);
  --card-bg: var(--color-surface);
  --card-border: var(--color-border);
  --input-bg: var(--color-surface);
  --input-border: var(--color-border);
}
```

## Dark Mode Toggle
```typescript
// $lib/theme/dark-mode.svelte.ts
let isDark = $state(false);

export function initDarkMode() {
  // Check localStorage first, then system preference
  const stored = localStorage.getItem('theme');
  if (stored) {
    isDark = stored === 'dark';
  } else {
    isDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
  }
  applyTheme();
}

export function toggleDarkMode() {
  isDark = !isDark;
  localStorage.setItem('theme', isDark ? 'dark' : 'light');
  applyTheme();
}

function applyTheme() {
  document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark', isDark);
}
```

## File Structure
```
$lib/theme/
├── tokens/
│   ├── primitives.css
│   ├── semantic.css
│   ├── components.css
│   └── dark.css
├── base.css (reset + defaults)
├── utilities.css
├── dark-mode.svelte.ts
└── index.css (imports all)
```

## Effort
Medium (M) - ~6-8 hours

SVG uploads skip magic number validation that other formats receive.

Security Impact: MIME type spoofing - attacker can upload malicious files with Content-Type: image/svg+xml

Location: packages/image-processing/src/service.ts:184-207

Fix: Call validateImageSignature() before processing SVG:
```typescript
if (mimeType === 'image/svg+xml') {
  if (!validateImageSignature(new Uint8Array(buffer), mimeType)) {
    throw new ValidationError('Invalid SVG file signature');
  }
  // ... rest of SVG processing
}
```

# Phase 4: SSR Hydration & Preloading Pattern

Implement proper SSR hydration for TanStack DB collections to avoid double-fetching.

## The Problem

Without proper hydration:
1. Server fetches data → renders HTML
2. Client hydrates → fetches AGAIN
3. User sees loading state → flash → content

With hydration:
1. Server fetches data → renders HTML
2. Client hydrates → uses server data
3. User sees content immediately

## Implementation

### Pattern 1: Server Load + Collection Hydration

**File: `apps/web/src/routes/library/+page.server.ts`**
```typescript
import { getUserLibrary } from '$lib/remote/library.remote';

export async function load() {
  // Fetch on server for SSR
  const library = await getUserLibrary();
  return { library };
}
```

**File: `apps/web/src/routes/library/+page.svelte`**
```svelte
<script>
  import { onMount } from 'svelte';
  import { useLiveQuery, libraryCollection } from '$lib/collections';
  import { queryClient } from '$lib/collections';

  let { data } = $props();

  // Hydrate collection with server data on mount
  onMount(() => {
    // Populate QueryClient cache with server data
    queryClient.setQueryData(['library'], data.library.items);
  });

  // Now useLiveQuery uses cached data (no refetch)
  const library = useLiveQuery((q) =>
    q.from({ item: libraryCollection })
  );
</script>

{#if library.isLoading}
  <!-- Only shows briefly during hydration -->
  <LibrarySkeleton />
{:else}
  {#each library.data as item (item.content.id)}
    <LibraryItem {item} />
  {/each}
{/if}
```

### Pattern 2: Collection Preload in Layout

**File: `apps/web/src/routes/library/+layout.ts`**
```typescript
import { browser } from '$app/environment';
import { libraryCollection } from '$lib/collections';

export async function load() {
  // Only preload in browser (SSR uses +page.server.ts)
  if (browser) {
    await libraryCollection.preload();
  }
  return {};
}
```

### Pattern 3: Streaming with Suspense Boundary

**File: `apps/web/src/routes/library/+page.svelte`**
```svelte
<script>
  import { getUserLibrary } from '$lib/remote/library.remote';
</script>

<!-- Uses await in template (experimental.async required) -->
<svelte:boundary>
  {#await getUserLibrary()}
    <LibrarySkeleton />
  {:then library}
    {#each library.items as item (item.content.id)}
      <LibraryItem {item} />
    {/each}
  {:catch error}
    <ErrorMessage {error} />
  {/await}

  {#snippet failed(error)}
    <ErrorMessage {error} />
  {/snippet}
</svelte:boundary>
```

## Best Practices

### When to Use Each Pattern

| Pattern | Use When |
|---------|----------|
| Server Load + Hydration | SEO matters, need full SSR |
| Collection Preload | Client-side nav, data not SEO-critical |
| Streaming Suspense | Large datasets, progressive loading |

### Avoiding Double Fetch

```typescript
// In +page.svelte
onMount(() => {
  // Check if data already in cache
  const cached = queryClient.getQueryData(['library']);
  if (!cached) {
    // Only fetch if not hydrated from server
    libraryCollection.preload();
  }
});
```

### Stale-While-Revalidate

```typescript
const library = useLiveQuery((q) =>
  q.from({ item: libraryCollection })
);

// Data is immediately available from cache
// Background refetch happens if stale
// UI updates reactively when new data arrives
```

## Verification

1. No "Loading..." flash on initial page load (SSR)
2. Network tab shows single request (not double)
3. Navigation to page uses cached data
4. Manual refresh fetches fresh data
5. staleTime respected for background refetch

## References

- [TanStack DB: collection.preload()](https://tanstack.com/db/latest/docs/reference/interfaces/Collection)
- [SvelteKit: Loading Data](https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/load)
- [Svelte: svelte:boundary](https://svelte.dev/docs/svelte/svelte-boundary)

# Phase 3.4: localStorage Progress Collection (Offline Support)

Create a localStorage-backed collection for playback progress that survives page close and works offline.

## Design Decision

**Why localStorage for progress?**
1. User closes tab mid-video → progress not lost
2. Network failure → progress still saved locally
3. Resume on any device → syncs when online
4. Instant UI → no network delay for progress bar

## Files to Create

### `apps/web/src/lib/collections/progress.ts`

```typescript
import { createCollection } from '@tanstack/svelte-db';
import { localStorageCollectionOptions } from '@tanstack/db';
import { savePlaybackProgress, getPlaybackProgress } from '$lib/remote/library.remote';

interface PlaybackProgress {
  contentId: string;
  positionSeconds: number;
  durationSeconds: number;
  completed: boolean;
  updatedAt: string;
  syncedAt: string | null;  // null = not yet synced
}

/**
 * Progress Collection (localStorage-backed)
 * 
 * Stores playback progress locally for offline support.
 * Syncs to server in background when online.
 */
export const progressCollection = createCollection(
  localStorageCollectionOptions<PlaybackProgress>({
    storageKey: 'codex-playback-progress',
    getKey: (item) => item.contentId,
  })
);

/**
 * Update progress (writes to localStorage immediately)
 */
export function updateLocalProgress(
  contentId: string,
  positionSeconds: number,
  durationSeconds: number
) {
  const now = new Date().toISOString();
  const completed = durationSeconds > 0 && (positionSeconds / durationSeconds) > 0.9;

  progressCollection.upsert({
    contentId,
    positionSeconds,
    durationSeconds,
    completed,
    updatedAt: now,
    syncedAt: null,  // Mark as unsynced
  });
}

/**
 * Sync unsynced progress to server
 * Call this periodically or on page visibility change
 */
export async function syncProgressToServer() {
  const unsynced = progressCollection.getAll().filter(p => !p.syncedAt);

  for (const progress of unsynced) {
    try {
      await savePlaybackProgress({
        contentId: progress.contentId,
        positionSeconds: progress.positionSeconds,
        durationSeconds: progress.durationSeconds,
      });

      // Mark as synced
      progressCollection.update(progress.contentId, (draft) => {
        draft.syncedAt = new Date().toISOString();
      });
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Failed to sync progress:', error);
      // Will retry next sync
    }
  }
}

/**
 * Merge server progress with local on page load
 * Server wins if newer, local wins if newer
 */
export async function mergeServerProgress(contentId: string) {
  const local = progressCollection.get(contentId);

  try {
    const server = await getPlaybackProgress(contentId);

    if (!server?.progress) {
      // No server progress, keep local
      return local;
    }

    if (!local) {
      // No local progress, use server
      progressCollection.insert({
        contentId,
        positionSeconds: server.progress.positionSeconds,
        durationSeconds: server.progress.durationSeconds,
        completed: server.progress.completed,
        updatedAt: server.progress.updatedAt,
        syncedAt: server.progress.updatedAt,
      });
      return server.progress;
    }

    // Both exist - compare timestamps
    const serverTime = new Date(server.progress.updatedAt).getTime();
    const localTime = new Date(local.updatedAt).getTime();

    if (serverTime > localTime) {
      // Server is newer - update local
      progressCollection.update(contentId, (draft) => {
        draft.positionSeconds = server.progress.positionSeconds;
        draft.durationSeconds = server.progress.durationSeconds;
        draft.completed = server.progress.completed;
        draft.updatedAt = server.progress.updatedAt;
        draft.syncedAt = server.progress.updatedAt;
      });
      return server.progress;
    } else {
      // Local is newer - will sync on next syncProgressToServer()
      return local;
    }
  } catch {
    // Offline - return local
    return local;
  }
}
```

### `apps/web/src/lib/collections/progress-sync.ts`

```typescript
import { browser } from '$app/environment';
import { syncProgressToServer } from './progress';

/**
 * Initialize progress sync
 * Call this once in root layout
 */
export function initProgressSync() {
  if (!browser) return;

  // Sync every 30 seconds while page is visible
  let syncInterval: number;

  function startSync() {
    syncInterval = setInterval(syncProgressToServer, 30000);
  }

  function stopSync() {
    clearInterval(syncInterval);
  }

  // Sync when page becomes visible
  document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', () => {
    if (document.visibilityState === 'visible') {
      syncProgressToServer();
      startSync();
    } else {
      stopSync();
      syncProgressToServer();  // Final sync before hide
    }
  });

  // Sync before page unload
  window.addEventListener('beforeunload', () => {
    syncProgressToServer();
  });

  // Start syncing
  startSync();

  // Initial sync
  syncProgressToServer();
}
```

## Usage Examples

### Video Player with Offline Progress
```svelte
<script>
  import { onMount } from 'svelte';
  import { 
    progressCollection, 
    updateLocalProgress, 
    mergeServerProgress 
  } from '$lib/collections/progress';

  let { data } = $props();
  let videoEl: HTMLVideoElement;
  let initialProgress: number | null = null;

  // Load and merge progress on mount
  onMount(async () => {
    const progress = await mergeServerProgress(data.content.id);
    if (progress) {
      initialProgress = progress.positionSeconds;
    }
  });

  // Set initial position when video is ready
  function handleLoadedMetadata() {
    if (initialProgress && videoEl) {
      videoEl.currentTime = initialProgress;
    }
  }

  // Save progress on time update (debounced externally)
  function handleTimeUpdate() {
    updateLocalProgress(
      data.content.id,
      videoEl.currentTime,
      videoEl.duration
    );
  }
</script>

<video
  bind:this={videoEl}
  src={data.streamingUrl}
  onloadedmetadata={handleLoadedMetadata}
  ontimeupdate={handleTimeUpdate}
/>
```

### Root Layout - Initialize Sync
```svelte
<!-- src/routes/+layout.svelte -->
<script>
  import { onMount } from 'svelte';
  import { initProgressSync } from '$lib/collections/progress-sync';

  onMount(() => {
    initProgressSync();
  });
</script>

<slot />
```

### Library Page - Show Local Progress
```svelte
<script>
  import { useLiveQuery } from '@tanstack/svelte-db';
  import { progressCollection } from '$lib/collections/progress';
  import { libraryCollection } from '$lib/collections/library';

  // Join library with local progress
  const library = useLiveQuery((q) =>
    q.from({ item: libraryCollection })
     .leftJoin(
       { progress: progressCollection },
       ({ item, progress }) => eq(item.content.id, progress.contentId)
     )
     .select(({ item, progress }) => ({
       content: item.content,
       progress: progress ?? item.progress,  // Prefer local, fallback to server
     }))
  );
</script>
```

## Key Concepts

### localStorage Collection
- Data persists in browser's localStorage
- Survives page close, browser restart
- Limited to ~5MB per origin
- Sync to server for cross-device access

### Sync Strategy
1. **Write** - Always write to localStorage first (instant)
2. **Sync** - Background sync every 30 seconds when visible
3. **Merge** - On page load, merge server state with local
4. **Conflict** - Newer timestamp wins

### Offline Detection
```typescript
if (navigator.onLine) {
  await syncProgressToServer();
} else {
  console.log('Offline - progress saved locally');
}
```

## Verification

1. Progress saves to localStorage immediately
2. Page refresh retains progress
3. Browser restart retains progress
4. Online sync updates server
5. Offline mode still saves locally
6. Merge correctly handles conflicts

## References

- [TanStack DB: localStorage Collection](https://tanstack.com/db/latest/docs/reference/functions/localStorageCollectionOptions)
- [Page Visibility API](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Page_Visibility_API)

## Objective

Enhance the basic org landing page (`_org/[slug]/(space)/+page.svelte`) with a hero section, featured content grid, org branding, and creator information. Transform the current placeholder into a fully branded, content-rich landing experience for each organization's subdomain.

---

## Phase 1: Layer & Domain Identification

### Layers Affected
- **Frontend (SvelteKit)**: Org landing page component
- **Remote Functions**: org.remote.ts, content.remote.ts
- **Backend (Dependent)**: Content-API for published content listing

### Domain
- **@codex/content** (featured content listing)
- **@codex/organization** (org details, branding)
- **Frontend**: apps/web/src/routes/_org/[slug]/(space)/

### Security Requirements
- Public access (no authentication required)
- Cacheable via CDN (public cache headers)

---

## Phase 2: Implementation Plan

### Step 1: Implement Server Load (+page.server.ts)

**File**: `apps/web/src/routes/_org/[slug]/(space)/+page.server.ts`

**Current State**: Only sets cache headers, no data fetching.

**Required Implementation**:
```typescript
import { redirect } from '@sveltejs/kit';
import { CACHE_HEADERS } from '/server/cache';
import { getPublicBranding } from '/remote/org.remote';

export async function load({ params, parent, platform }) {
  const { slug } = params;
  const parentData = await parent();

  // Fetch org branding from KV cache
  const branding = await getPublicBranding(slug);

  if (!branding) {
    throw redirect(307, '/?error=org-not-found');
  }

  // TODO: Wire to content API once Codex-qv2 is complete
  // const featuredContent = await listPublicOrgContent(slug, { limit: 6 });
  const featuredContent: any[] = []; // Mock for now

  return {
    org: parentData.org,
    branding,
    featuredContent,
  };
}

export const actions = {};
```

**Key Points**:
- Use `getPublicBranding(slug)` for KV-cached org branding
- Featured content will be mocked until Codex-qv2 (public content endpoint) is complete
- Maintain `CACHE_HEADERS.DYNAMIC_PUBLIC` for CDN caching

---

